    { phase: 'Verify', label: `fix#${i + 1}` },
  )
}

phase('Review')
const review = await agent(
  `${COMMON}\n${CONTRACT}\n${DESIGN}\n
Adversarially review the plan-mode feature diff for correctness and faithfulness to the design. Run \`cd ${ROOT} && git diff --stat\` and inspect the new/changed files: src/minima/plan_session.ts, src/minima/plan_council.ts, src/minima/index.ts, src/cli/main.ts, src/tui/app.tsx, tests/plan_session.test.ts, tests/plan_council.test.ts. Check specifically: (a) NO database — grep confirms plan_session.ts / plan_council.ts / the tests never import bun:sqlite, MinimaDb, or ../db/minima_db.ts; plan_session.ts uses a local crypto.randomUUID() for ids; (b) researchers are constrained read-only via tool_allowlist (no way for a council spawn to write during plan mode); (c) meta/critic/synth calls use the fixed metaModel via complete() and never route or re-rank RoutingResult (propensity integrity); (d) the finalize .md is written directly (Bun.write), NOT through the agent tool loop, so the read-only block can't block it; (e) the planner system prompt is re-anchored each plan turn and RESTORED (no cross-turn leak) on approve/cancel/exit; (f) council failure is fail-open (falls back to a plain planner turn); (g) abort (Esc) tears down the council controller; (h) non-plan-mode turns behave exactly as before. Report as a findings list (most severe first) with file:line and a concrete failure scenario for each; if a finding is a real defect, FIX it directly and re-run \`bun run check && bun run lint && bun test\` to confirm still green. If you find nothing real, say so. Report the final diff --stat and test status.`,
